# Global guardrails

- Make the smallest safe change that solves the requested problem.
- Do not rewrite, refactor, rename, or reorganize unrelated files unless explicitly asked.
- Before non-trivial changes, explain the plan and the files that will be touched.
- Never invent business facts about KYIRA ENERGIES. Use placeholders or TODOs for unknown data.
- Keep code readable, typed, maintainable, and easy to modify after client feedback.
- Do not add dependencies unless they clearly reduce complexity or risk.
- Never expose secrets, API keys, SMTP credentials, tokens, or private client data in source code.
- Prefer simple, boring, production-ready code over clever abstractions.
